properties.Summary:
Description: Mixed bag of precipitation and strong winds Friday. Quebec City will receive between 10 and 15 centimetres of snow in addition to experiencing a more or less extended period of freezing rain on Friday morning. Areas north of Quebec City will receive snowfall amounts of up to 25 centimetres. Easterly winds gusting up to 70 kilometres per hour will accompany the snow and cause reduced visibilities in blowing snow. For their part, areas south of the St. Lawrence River will receive mostly rain. ### Winter storm warnings are issued when multiple types of severe winter weather are expected to occur together. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant rain expected today. Rain will begin early this morning. Across most areas, the rain will end early this afternoon.
